by Valentine Z » Mon Apr 06, 2020 2:11 am

North German Realm wrote:They have ten active aircraft carriers, making their navy more powerful than any OTL country other than the USA which has like, 11.

Interesting note on the personnel count and the percentages.

Federal Army 400,000 Active, 42,312 Deployed.
Federal Navy 235,000 Active, 20,000 Deployed.
Federal Air Force 115,000 Active, 12,688 Deployed.

Interesting percentages, in the sense that they give a [10.578, 8.5106383, 11.033043] in terms of percentage ( # Deployed / # Active * 100 ), so I guess I learned that the Federal personnel more or less have 8-12% of their troops deployed at any one time.

Also of note is how they don't seem to have a rank of Private. The inverted-V ranks are instead used for Sergeants and higher, while the slanted bars (normally reserved for officers) are used for the lower ranks. At least, in comparison to RL Singapore, the V's are used from Lance Corporals to Sergeants and Warrant Officers, while the Horizontal bars are for Officers (1-3 bars, from 2nd Lt, 1st Lt, Cpt.) Something for me to wonder about!

EDIT: I realised that they are Rank insignias of the German Bundeswehr. Ahh, TIL.

-----

AN: The fact that they have a contingency plan to ensure their survival in the event of a disaster on an universe-scale. Seeds / ships that they can fire and move to other multiverses in order to find a new place or an universe to stay in. The only thing I can wonder is - what are the % survival rates of the seeds? What if they went to multiverses where the laws of physics do not allow life at all? Are there preliminary analysers to make sure that you don't go to a dud universe?
